3. Define scope — if the question is too broad to get a useful answer, narrow it. If it is too narrow to make sense on its own, widen it slightly.
4. Fix grammar, spelling, and punctuation.
5. Use plain, direct language. Cut filler words and unnecessary qualifiers.
6. If the question has multiple parts, separate them clearly.

